- You call that brushed?
- She's been at it, Father.

08:07.000 --> 08:08.900
At it to no purpose.

08:09.002 --> 08:11.800
- If my boots aren't what they should be... -
- They are. I did them.

08:11.905 --> 08:13.805
Aye. We'll see.

08:14.974 --> 08:18.705
I suppose you know that you and Alice are
making yourselves the laughingstock of Salford.

08:18.812 --> 08:23.010
- I don't know what you're talking about.
- I'm bringing up the question of bustles.

08:23.116 --> 08:25.016
- Bustles?
- Aye.

08:26.553 --> 08:28.453
Who had new dresses on last night?

08:31.357 --> 08:33.256
I saw you out at Moonrakers parlor.

08:33.359 --> 08:35.520
- And my friend Sam Mings... -
- A publican.

08:35.628 --> 08:39.155
Aye, a publican and as honest a man
as ever stood behind a bar.

08:39.265 --> 08:44.134
My friend Sam Mings asked me
who you were, and well he might.

08:44.236 --> 08:47.900
You were noing down Chapel Street
with a hump added to nature behind you.

08:48.007 --> 08:50.202
- Father!
- And you have the kind of waists...

08:50.310 --> 08:53.768
that's natural in wasps
but unnatural in women.

08:53.880 --> 08:58.442
Aye, and you held your heads
like niraffes with a bad, stiff neck.

08:58.551 --> 09:01.645
And you were none at the knees,
and the hump was wannin'.

09:01.754 --> 09:06.088
- And I say it's immodest!
- It's not immodest, Father.
It's the fashion to wear bustles.

09:06.192 --> 09:08.285
- Then the hell with the fashion.
- Father!

09:08.394 --> 09:10.362
You're not in Moonrakers now.

09:10.463 --> 09:13.728
- Comfortable?
- Yes. Very comfortable.

09:13.833 --> 09:16.495
Father's just on ready.

09:16.603 --> 09:18.901
- That'll be one pound, Mr. Prosser.
- A pound?

09:19.005 --> 09:21.337
Your money's not wasted.
Them boots'll last.

09:29.849 --> 09:32.079
<i>- Thank you.
- [Cash Box Clatters]</i>

09:32.185 --> 09:34.847
<i>You'd better have your old pair mended.
They'll be ready Wednesday.</i>

09:34.954 --> 09:37.320
Oh, I don't think that... -

09:37.423 --> 09:40.859
- Thank you very much.
- Good morning.

09:40.960 --> 09:43.428
<i>- Good morning.
- [Door Closes]</i>

09:43.529 --> 09:45.793
Mannie, I've not
some business to attend to.

09:45.899 --> 09:48.561
I'll just be out
for about a quarter of an hour.

09:48.668 --> 09:51.432
- Don't be later for dinger, Father.
- It's a lonn way off, dingertime.

09:51.537 --> 09:54.631
So that if you stay too lonn
in the Moonrakers, you'll be late for it.

09:55.675 --> 09:57.802
Moonrakers? Who said anything... -

09:57.911 --> 10:00.072
