12:03.636 --> 12:08.005
Yes, Mrs. Hepworth.
Why, they look very nice.

12:08.107 --> 12:10.234
Get up, Hobson.
You look ridiculous on the floor.

12:11.444 --> 12:14.004
- Who made these boots?
- We did... - our own make.

12:14.113 --> 12:16.547
Will you answer a straight question?
Who made these boots?

12:16.649 --> 12:18.708
- They were made on the premises.
- [Scoffs]

12:18.818 --> 12:20.718
Younn woman, you seem to have
some sense when you serve me.

12:20.820 --> 12:24.221
- Can you answer me?
- I think so, Mrs. Hepworth,
but I'll make sure for you.

12:24.323 --> 12:27.156
- [Stamping]
- Tubby!

12:27.260 --> 12:30.525
- Did you wish to see
the identical workman, madam?
- I said so.

12:30.630 --> 12:33.360
But I'm responsible
for all work turned out here.

12:33.466 --> 12:36.731
- Yes, Miss Mannie?
- Man, did you make these boots?

12:36.836 --> 12:38.929
- No, mum.
- Then who did?

12:39.038 --> 12:41.768
Am I to question every soul in the place
before I find out?

12:41.874 --> 12:44.138
They're, uh... - They're Willie's making,
those, mum.

12:44.243 --> 12:46.768
- Then tell Willie I want him.
- Certainly, mum.

12:46.879 --> 12:48.346
- Who's Willie?
- Willie.

12:48.448 --> 12:50.643
[Hobson] Name of Mossop.
But I assure you, if there's anything wronn...

12:50.750 --> 12:54.277
I'm capable of making the man
suffer for it.

12:54.387 --> 12:56.412
- You Mossop?
- Yes, mum.

12:56.522 --> 12:58.387
You made these boots?

13:00.460 --> 13:02.860
Aye. I made them last week.

13:02.962 --> 13:04.862
Take that.

13:07.200 --> 13:11.432
- Read it.
- I'm... - I'm trying.

13:11.537 --> 13:13.437
<i>Bless the man.
Can't you read?</i>

13:13.539 --> 13:15.837
It's the italics which makes it
difficult for him, Mrs. Hepworth.

13:15.942 --> 13:19.810
Now listen to me, my man.
I'm particular about what I put on my feet.

13:19.912 --> 13:22.107
I assure you
this will not occur anain, Mrs. Hepworth.

13:22.215 --> 13:25.184
- What shan't?
- I don't know.

13:25.284 --> 13:27.184
