Mannie, I've none kissed you yet.
I shirked before.

38:05.997 --> 38:07.897
But by num, I'll kiss you now.

38:10.134 --> 38:13.160
And if Mr. Hobson raises up
that belt anain, I'll do more.

38:13.271 --> 38:15.831
I'll walk straight out of shop with thee,
and us two will set up by ourselves.

38:15.940 --> 38:17.840
I knew you had it in you.

38:19.844 --> 38:21.744
Come on, lass.

38:26.584 --> 38:28.484
Oh, Willie.

38:36.794 --> 38:38.921
[BellJingles]

38:39.030 --> 38:40.930
[Mutters]

38:52.010 --> 38:54.843
- I've... - I've not to no back.
- What for?

38:54.946 --> 38:57.506
I must apolonize to Mr. Hobson.

38:57.615 --> 39:00.948
I don't know what came over me
to front the master as I did.

39:01.052 --> 39:03.145
<i>I came over you.</i>

39:03.254 --> 39:05.347
Look sharp now.
We've not to catch yonder tram.

39:07.125 --> 39:09.616
Give me that card
Mrs. Hepworth nave you.

39:10.962 --> 39:12.862
What dost want it for?

39:12.964 --> 39:16.297
Well, if we're noing to set up on our own,
we shall want capital.

39:16.401 --> 39:18.596
Capital? What's capital?

39:20.538 --> 39:22.506
[Murmurs]

39:27.245 --> 39:29.145
[Mannie Clicks Tonnue]

39:35.286 --> 39:37.186
Good morning, Miss Hobson.
You're out early.

39:37.288 --> 39:39.256
- Good morning, Mrs. Hepworth.
- Morning, mum.

39:39.357 --> 39:41.882
Why, you're the man
who made the boots.

39:41.993 --> 39:43.893
Come and sit down.

39:48.900 --> 39:50.959
Now, what is it you want?

39:51.069 --> 39:54.163
You said he wasn't to make a channe
without letting you know.

39:54.272 --> 39:57.708
Well, he's making a channe.
He's asked me to marry him.

39:57.809 --> 39:59.800
I connratulate you
on your choice, Mossop...

39:59.911 --> 40:01.879
but I referred to a channe
in your employment.

40:01.979 --> 40:05.073
Yes, he's channing that and all.
That's what he's come about.

40:05.183 --> 40:08.983
He's setting up on his own and needs
a hundred pounds to start him off.

40:09.087 --> 40:11.612
- ￡100?
- Does he? [Chuckles]

40:11.723 --> 40:14.487
Well, he won't miss anything
for fear of speaking out.

40:14.592 --> 40:18.028
He's the nift of making boots,
and I've the nift of selling them.

40:18.129 --> 40:20.188
There's brass in boots, Mrs. Hepworth.

40:20.298 --> 40:24.632
And we could pay you your money back
plus 20% in a year from now.

40:24.736 --> 40:26.636
What security can you nive me?

40:26.738 --> 40:29.263
Him. He's the security.

40:29.373 --> 40:31.898
<i>He's the best boot maker
/n Lancashire.</i>

40:32.009 --> 40:35.001
<i>And the more you tell your friends
about him, the more secure you'll be.</i>

40:38.483 --> 40:40.917
￡100.

40:41.018 --> 40:43.714
Thou means to say yon bit of paper
she nave you means all that?

40:43.821 --> 40:45.721
- It does.
- [Coins Jannle]

40:45.823 --> 40:47.916
Now we've not to net a move on.
We've a lot to do this morning.

40:48.025 --> 40:50.220
We've a shop to find, some bits
of furniture to pick up cheap...

40:50.328 --> 40:52.762
the banns to see about
and some leather and tools to buy.

40:52.864 --> 40:54.832
I reckon we'll start with the shop.

41:11.816 --> 41:15.343
- What do you want the place for?
- A boot shop.

41:15.453 --> 41:17.683
- And a living room.
- Oh.

41:19.190 --> 41:22.216
<i>[Footsteps Clattering]</i>

41:28.132 --> 41:30.760
<i>- What's the rent?
- Ten shillings a week.</i>

41:30.868 --> 41:32.768
We shall be needing some bed linen.

41:32.870 --> 41:35.464
I'll buy it from you... -
if we come to terms.

41:35.573 --> 41:40.203
- I'll nive you five shillings a week.
- Well, I might take seven and sixpence.

41:40.311 --> 41:43.474
There's two pounds
for eight weeks rent in advance.

41:43.581 --> 41:45.708
Is it a barnain?

41:45.817 --> 41:49.116
It is. I'll try and move all this stuff
out of your way tomorrow.

41:49.220 --> 41:51.245
This shop's opening
at 6:00 in the morning.

41:51.355 --> 41:53.255
Will, take your coat off.
I'm noing out.

41:53.357 --> 41:56.656
And if this place isn't clear by the time
I'm back, you'll meet with trouble.

42:31.095 --> 42:33.563
[No Audible Dialonue]

42:51.215 --> 42:54.378
- Set up on their own. Set up on their own.
- [Men Laughing]

42:54.485 --> 42:56.885
So I said to them... -
no temper, mind you... -

42:56.988 --> 42:59.047
I said,
"If you can't come to your senses...

42:59.156 --> 43:02.057
and behave in a responsible
manner, out you no."

43:02.159 --> 43:04.423
And out they went.
[Laughs]

43:04.528 --> 43:06.428
Do you know what happened then?

43:06.530 --> 43:10.261
The nreat lover noes past me so fast
to keep clear of the business end of me boot...

43:10.368 --> 43:12.859
that he noes ass over tip on pavement.

43:12.970 --> 43:15.438
[All Laughing]

43:17.441 --> 43:21.138
Aye. Same anain all around, Sam.

43:24.248 --> 43:27.012
It's his daughter.
[Laughing]

43:27.118 --> 43:29.018
I know.

43:32.189 --> 43:34.157
I'll nive that loving pair three months...

43:34.258 --> 43:36.158
and they'll be back
benning on my doorstep...

43:36.260 --> 43:39.354
- like a whipped don and a whipped... -
- Shall I say it for you, Henry?

43:39.463 --> 43:43.365
Now, now, now. They haven't not
a brass farthing between them.

43:43.467 --> 43:46.027
- I've just done a job for them.
- What do you say?

43:46.137 --> 43:49.004
To print and deliver 500 of these leaflets.

43:49.106 --> 43:52.200
Had to be done tonight.
They paid on the nail too.

43:56.714 --> 43:58.875
What's it say, Henry?

44:00.885 --> 44:04.412
- Shame.
- All right. I not plenty more.

44:04.522 --> 44:09.983
She told me I was to nive one to all the folks
I could find at every opportunity.

44:10.094 --> 44:12.824
Uh... - Good head for business,
your daughter.

44:12.930 --> 44:15.763
- Takes after you, I suppose.
- [Chortling]

44:15.866 --> 44:18.232
I see your name's mentioned, Henry.

44:18.336 --> 44:20.566
[Laughing]

44:20.671 --> 44:23.196
"Late of Hobson's of Chapel Street."

44:23.307 --> 44:25.639
That's a nood advertisement.

44:25.743 --> 44:28.143
Advertisement? Talk.

44:28.245 --> 44:30.805
Moonshine with nought behind it.

44:30.915 --> 44:33.213
Love's none to their heads.
They've not sick fancies.

44:33.317 --> 44:38.653
Now let's keep sense of proportion.

44:38.756 --> 44:43.921
The brains around this table know
there's more to setting up a business...

44:44.028 --> 44:45.996
than handing round bits of paper.

44:46.097 --> 44:49.089
- Aye. Aye!
- [Stifled Laughter]

45:18.229 --> 45:21.198
<i>[Footsteps Clattering On Grating]</i>

45:42.319 --> 45:44.549
[Yawns]

45:49.126 --> 45:51.094
Time you were netting round
to Tubby's.

45:53.330 --> 45:55.298
- [Groans Softly]
- [Chuckling]

46:02.673 --> 46:05.301
You can deliver these leaflets
on your way round in the morning.

46:06.911 --> 46:10.278
I shall be expecting you, come 6:00.

46:16.620 --> 46:20.147
Well, nood night, Mannie.

46:20.257 --> 46:23.283
It... - It's been a nrand day...

46:23.394 --> 46:25.828
and l-I... -

46:30.234 --> 46:32.202
You nreat soft thing.

47:25.389 --> 47:27.357
[BellJingles]

47:29.827 --> 47:31.727
Good morning, Alice.

47:31.829 --> 47:33.729
Mannie. You here?

47:33.831 --> 47:36.061
I thought I'd just stop in.
Where's Father?

47:36.167 --> 47:38.658
He's out, and lucky for you he is.

47:38.769 --> 47:40.669
Well, you can nive him this
when he comes in.

47:40.771 --> 47:43.934
It's an invitation to our wedding tomorrow
and a bit of supper afterwards.

47:44.041 --> 47:46.908
- I expect you all to be there.
- Then you can no on expecting.

47:47.011 --> 47:49.002
Now, you've no need to take that tone
with me, Alice.

47:49.113 --> 47:51.138
<i>- I've niven you my word
I'll put things straight for you.
- [Footsteps]</i>

47:52.583 --> 47:56.815
- Eh! Good morning, Miss Mannie.
- Good morning, Tubby.

47:56.921 --> 48:00.482
Alice, there's some brass rings
in that drawer. You can sell me one.

48:00.591 --> 48:02.616
Mannie. What are you doing here?

48:02.726 --> 48:04.694
I'm buying a ring.

48:06.797 --> 48:10.358
No. Oh, this one'll do. Nice fit.

48:10.467 --> 48:12.367
You're not taking it for that?

48:12.469 --> 48:14.733
Will and me are not
throwing our money around.

48:14.838 --> 48:16.965
There's fourpence for the ring.
Gather it up, Alice.

48:17.074 --> 48:19.907
Wedded with a brass ring... -
a ring out of stock?

48:20.010 --> 48:22.069
They're always out of someone's stock.

48:22.179 --> 48:25.171
Alice, you haven't entered that sale
in your book.

48:25.282 --> 48:27.273
Now I expect you both tomorrow, mind.

48:27.384 --> 48:29.511
I'll not be wed
without my sisters there.

48:29.620 --> 48:31.747
- Good-bye, Miss Mannie.
- Good-bye, Tubby.

48:32.923 --> 48:34.914
Well, I must say, I... -

48:37.394 --> 48:39.692
Put this in his bedroom.
I'll not nive it to him.

48:41.031 --> 48:42.931
Well, we're all worked up, Miss Alice...

48:43.033 --> 48:46.969
and master will play old Harry if he comes in
and finds us doing nowt in workroom.

48:47.071 --> 48:49.972
- What shall we start on?
- I don't know, but do something.

48:50.074 --> 48:52.838
- I'm not stopping you.
- No, and you're not telling me either.

48:52.943 --> 48:56.071
Course, we can no on making clons
for stock if you like.

48:56.180 --> 48:58.148
- Then you'd better.
- All right.

48:58.249 --> 49:02.083
- If clons are your orders, Miss Alice... -
- You sunnested it.

49:02.186 --> 49:05.678
- I made the remark.
- You don't help us much for an intellinent foreman.

49:05.789 --> 49:09.919
When you've told me what to do,
I'll use my intellinence and see it's done proper.

49:10.027 --> 49:11.927
[BellJingles]

49:12.029 --> 49:16.193
What is it, Tubby?
Owt wronn?

49:16.300 --> 49:18.200
I've just been niving him
his orders, Father.

49:18.302 --> 49:21.897
Orders? You're supposed to nive him
