49:22.006 --> 49:25.737
Well, net back down now
and start doing what she told you.

49:25.843 --> 49:27.743
And look sharp.

49:33.984 --> 49:35.884
<i>- Vicky.
- Yes, Father?</i>

49:35.986 --> 49:37.453
Dinger.

49:37.554 --> 49:39.988
<i>[Clock Chiming]</i>

49:49.967 --> 49:51.935
[Sighs]

49:59.677 --> 50:02.441
- What's that?
- Jellied tonnue, Father.

50:02.546 --> 50:05.481
Don't make jokes about food.

50:05.582 --> 50:08.813
- We have roast pork Mondays.
- Well, it's cold tonnue today, Father.

50:08.919 --> 50:11.717
- You made me the cook.
- I put you in place of cook.

50:11.822 --> 50:13.722
Thou's not made cook yet, my lass.

50:13.824 --> 50:16.258
I'm not hanning over the stove all day.
I've not my looks to think of.

50:16.360 --> 50:20.888
Thou's not nowt to think of but
providing me with my rightful home comforts.

50:22.566 --> 50:25.262
- What's for puddin'?
- Rhubarb.

50:27.871 --> 50:31.466
Alice. Why is my dinger no dinger?

50:31.575 --> 50:34.476
I can't help it. I've not the shop
to look after, and that's a full-time job.

50:34.578 --> 50:36.603
You can't expect us to fill Mannie's place
and our own.

50:36.714 --> 50:40.013
I've not all the housework to do. Do you expect
two pairs of hands to do the work of three?

50:40.117 --> 50:43.746
- I'm busy enough keeping the books and finures.
- I've the beds to make and floors to clean.

50:43.854 --> 50:45.947
Now stop!
I'll not listen to any more.

50:46.056 --> 50:51.619
Three weeks I've stood of this... - perversity,
disobedience, incompetence and bad cooking.

50:51.729 --> 50:54.323
And I'll not stand it anymore!

50:54.431 --> 50:57.889
I'm noing to where
I can net comfort, nood food...

50:58.001 --> 51:00.401
and the respect that's due to me.

51:00.504 --> 51:06.067
I'm noing to Moonrakers,
and I shall not be back till late tonight.

51:16.553 --> 51:18.453
[BellJingles]

51:41.812 --> 51:45.009
<i>- §§ [People Singing]
- [Tudsbury] Thinking things over...</i>

51:45.115 --> 51:47.083
<i>I'm not surprised, for one.</i>

51:47.184 --> 51:49.516
Mind you, I could see it coming
with Mannie.

51:49.620 --> 51:51.918
She's a sharp and nrasping nature.

51:52.022 --> 51:54.422
- And what's she not out of it?
- Aye.

51:54.525 --> 51:57.426
- Salford's brightest hope.
- [Chortling]

51:57.528 --> 51:59.689
Can't read, can't write.

51:59.797 --> 52:01.697
[All Laughing]

52:01.799 --> 52:04.734
Mannie never had
no sense of style.

52:04.835 --> 52:07.463
Now, other two's quite different.

52:07.571 --> 52:11.371
You mean they're out to catch the eye
in Tudsbury's latest.

52:12.709 --> 52:15.678
Vicky doesn't need a bustle for that.

52:15.779 --> 52:17.906
My friends.

52:18.015 --> 52:20.779
- Hear! Hear!
- Good old Henry.

52:20.884 --> 52:24.445
- And a wonderful little band you are.
- Aye.

52:24.555 --> 52:27.285
Tudsbury, the expert on women...

52:27.391 --> 52:31.452
just because he spends his life
fitting on their petticoats.

52:31.562 --> 52:35.225
You're nowt
but an old woman yourself, Tudsbury.

52:35.332 --> 52:37.232
<i>[Heeler]
Now, now, Henry.</i>

52:40.137 --> 52:43.368
As for you, you're nowt but a shadow.

52:43.474 --> 52:47.535
Our Mannie saw through you years ano... -
totting at me heels...

52:47.644 --> 52:51.546
buttering me up with your "Yes, Henry"
and your "No, Henry"...

52:51.648 --> 52:54.776
all for sake of free drinks you net.

52:54.885 --> 52:55.977
[Snorting Laugh]

52:59.122 --> 53:02.319
Looking for pink rats, Denton?

53:02.426 --> 53:05.623
You're the bingest old soak in Salford.

53:05.729 --> 53:07.754
[Wheezing Laugh]

53:07.865 --> 53:10.197
You're rotten with alcohol...

53:10.300 --> 53:13.599
rotten as the fish
you sell on Mondays.

53:13.704 --> 53:15.672
Now then, Henry,
that's enough of that.

53:15.772 --> 53:17.672
Fish. That's what I am.

53:17.774 --> 53:19.435
<i>- §§ [Ends]
- [Laughter]</i>

53:19.543 --> 53:22.671
Bin fish, little pond.

53:25.716 --> 53:31.677
It's a stinking little pond,
and I'm netting out of it!

53:38.428 --> 53:40.487
<i>[Sam]
No /ll feeling, gentlemen, I hope.</i>

53:40.597 --> 53:42.497
<i>We all know Henry.</i>

53:43.534 --> 53:46.264
<i>Once wedding's over tomorrow,
you'll feel better.</i>

53:46.370 --> 53:47.928
[Chuckling]

53:49.106 --> 53:52.371
As for you, Sam Mings...

53:52.476 --> 53:56.412
my Mary always said you were a robber,
and you are.

53:56.513 --> 53:58.413
- Systematic swindling!
- Shh! Henry!

53:58.515 --> 54:00.415
That's what it is.

54:00.517 --> 54:03.645
We all of us pay too much for drinks
once we've had a few.

54:03.754 --> 54:08.817
[Chuckles] Poor old Denton
hasn't had right channe for 20 years.

54:08.926 --> 54:11.486
[Wheezing Laugh]

54:14.665 --> 54:16.792
I'm off.

57:17.447 --> 57:20.746
[No Audible Dialonue]

57:22.652 --> 57:24.620
<i>[Loud Thud]</i>

57:36.032 --> 57:38.000
<i>[Factory Whistle Blows]</i>

57:46.543 --> 57:48.511
[No Audible Dialonue]

57:55.385 --> 57:57.353
<i>[Snoring]</i>

58:04.361 --> 58:06.829
[Snoring Continues]

58:27.918 --> 58:29.886
[Sighs]

58:33.857 --> 58:35.984
Oh. Good.

58:36.092 --> 58:38.356
Are you coming to my wedding
with a face like that?

58:38.461 --> 58:41.021
You let me in, and perhaps
your face will be like mine.

58:41.131 --> 58:44.123
It's your father.
He's asleep in our cellar.

58:44.234 --> 58:46.429
Oh, come in.
That won't upset my face.

58:47.571 --> 58:50.438
<i>- Well, go on.
- Well, I daren't leave him there any lonner.</i>

58:50.540 --> 58:52.565
